.TH SYOPCTL 8 "September 2024" "v0.1.0" "System Management"
.SH NAME
sysopctl \- Manage system resources and tasks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysopctl
[COMMAND] [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sysopctl is a command to manage system services, processes, and system health.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B service list
List all running services
.TP
.B service start \fI<name>\fR
Start a service specified by \fI<name>\fR.
.TP
.B service stop \fI<name>\fR
Stop a service specified by \fI<name>\fR.
.TP
.B system load
View system load averages
.TP
.B disk usage
Check disk usage statistics by partition
.TP
.B process monitor
Monitor system processes in real-time
.TP
.B logs analyze
Analyze recent critical log entries
.TP
.B backup \fI<path>\fR
Backup system files from \fI<path>\fR to a predefined backup location
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --help
Display this help message
.TP
.B --version
Show version information
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sysopctl service list
Lists all active services
.TP
.B sysopctl service start apache2
Starts the Apache2 service
.TP
.B sysopctl system load
Displays the current system load averages
.TP
.B sysopctl disk usage
Shows disk usage statistics
.TP
.B sysopctl process monitor
Provides real-time monitoring of system processes
.TP
.B sysopctl logs analyze
Analyzes critical log entries from the past hour
.TP
.B sysopctl backup /home/user
Backs up files from /home/user
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR uptime (1),
.BR df (1),
.BR top (1),
.BR journalctl (1),
.BR rsync (1)
